              </figure>
              
              <!-- end MainFigure -->
              <!-- ArticleWrapper -->
              <div class="article__wrapper">
                
                <!-- Paragraphs -->
                
                <script async src='https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2184560724232610' crossorigin='anonymous'></script><ins class='adsbygoogle' style='display:block; text-align:center;' data-ad-layout='in-article' data-ad-format='fluid' data-ad-client='ca-pub-2184560724232610' data-ad-slot='6172469131'></ins><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
                
                
                <p>This crispy cabbage pie delivers comfort and flavor in every bite with a golden crust and creamy, herby sauce. The first forkful always surprises me with how something so humble can feel so special, especially when shared on chilly evenings.</p>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <aside id="paragraph-2" class="note">
                  <h2 class="icon-wrapper txt-xl">
                      <svg class="icon icon--medium"><use href="/assets/drawable/symbols-v7.svg?#note"></use></svg>
                      <span>Why You’ll Love This Recipe</span>
                  </h2>
                  <ul><li>Easy to make with just one bowl and skillet</li><li>Perfect for weeknight dinners or weekend brunch</li><li>Flexible use your favorite cheese or go dairy-free</li><li>Vegetarian and great for meal prep</li><li>Pairs beautifully with the fresh dill sauce</li></ul>
                </aside>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <p>I whipped this up after a fridge cleanout one rainy Sunday, and it immediately became a regular request. Even my kids reach for seconds every time.</p>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <h2 id="paragraph-4" class="txt-xxl">Ingredients</h2>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <script async src='https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2184560724232610' crossorigin='anonymous'></script><ins class='adsbygoogle' style='display:block; text-align:center;' data-ad-layout='in-article' data-ad-format='fluid' data-ad-client='ca-pub-2184560724232610' data-ad-slot='4371639595'></ins><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
                
                
                <ul><li><strong>Cabbage:</strong> choose a fresh head that feels heavy for its size and has crisp leaves for best flavor and texture</li><li><strong>Green onions:</strong> offer a mild bite and a pop of color go for firm bright stalks</li><li><strong>Eggs:</strong> provide richness and help bind everything together use large eggs for structure</li><li><strong>Dijon mustard:</strong> turns up the zing opt for smooth over grainy for a silky finish</li><li><strong>Salt and pepper:</strong> round out the flavors always taste for seasoning at the end</li><li><strong>Flour:</strong> keeps the pie together after slicing use a high-quality gluten-free blend if needed</li><li><strong>Baking powder:</strong> adds lift and lightness so the pie is not dense</li><li><strong>Olive oil:</strong> creates crisp edges and a nice golden finish choose a fruity extra virgin kind</li><li><strong>Optional cheese:</strong> brings extra creaminess try a sharp cheddar or mild mozzarella shredded fresh from the block</li><li><strong>Light sour cream:</strong> forms the tangy base of the sauce try organic for fuller flavor</li><li><strong>Mayonnaise:</strong> makes the sauce extra smooth pick a full-fat version if possible</li><li><strong>Fresh dill:</strong> infuses the sauce with herbal brightness and aroma always use fresh dill not dried for the best sauce</li></ul>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <p>Make sure your cabbage is shredded finely so it cooks evenly and binds well</p>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <h2 id="paragraph-7" class="txt-xxl">Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <dl><dt><strong>Prepare the Vegetables:</strong></dt><dd>Shred the cabbage finely and chop the green onions then place both into a large mixing bowl cutting any long cabbage strips for easy eating</dd><dt><strong>Mix the Egg Base:</strong></dt><dd>Crack the eggs into a smaller bowl add Dijon mustard salt and pepper whisk until smooth and pour this mixture over the cabbage and green onions tossing until all vegetables are well coated</dd><dt><strong>Combine Dry Ingredients:</strong></dt><dd>Sprinkle flour and baking powder over the cabbage mixture gently toss everything so the flour and baking powder disappear into the mix with no dry streaks</dd><dt><strong>Cook the Pie:</strong></dt><dd>Heat two tablespoons of olive oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat spread the cabbage mixture evenly in the skillet pressing down firmly with a spatula set heat to low-medium cover with a lid or foil and cook for about fifteen minutes until the bottom is golden brown and crisp</dd><dt><strong>Flip and Finish:</strong></dt><dd>Carefully loosen the pie with a spatula lay a plate or cutting board over the skillet and flip the pie onto it add a bit more oil to the skillet then slide the pie back in cooked side now facing up sprinkle cheese over top now if using and return to the heat uncovered let it finish cooking another ten to fifteen minutes for a deep crisp on both sides</dd><dt><strong>Make the Dill Cream Sauce:</strong></dt><dd>In a small bowl stir together sour cream mayonnaise chopped dill and a little salt and pepper until smooth and creamy taste and adjust seasoning to your liking</dd><dt><strong>Serve and Enjoy:</strong></dt><dd>Allow the pie to cool just slightly before slicing serve warm with a generous spoonful or drizzle of dill cream sauce and more fresh dill or green onions to garnish</dd></dl>
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <script async src='https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-2184560724232610' crossorigin='anonymous'></script><ins class='adsbygoogle' style='display:block; text-align:center;' data-ad-layout='in-article' data-ad-format='fluid' data-ad-client='ca-pub-2184560724232610' data-ad-slot='3058557920'></ins><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
                
                
                
                <figure id="paragraph-9" class="txt-s pin-wrapper">
