                <aside id="paragraph-21" class="note">
                  <h2 class="icon-wrapper txt-xl">
                      <svg class="icon icon--medium"><use href="/assets/drawable/symbols-v7.svg?#note"></use></svg>
                      <span>Pro Tips</span>
                  </h2>
                  <ul><li>Always shred your cabbage extra fine for even cooking and better pie structure</li><li>Let the pie rest a few minutes before slicing to keep each wedge intact</li><li>Do not skimp on fresh dill in the sauce it really brings the whole dish together</li></ul>
                </aside>
                
                
                
                
                <!-- end Paragraphs -->
                
                
                <!-- Faqs -->
                <h2 id="faqs" class="txt-xxl">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                <dl>
                  
                  <dt>→ How do I get the cabbage pie crisp?</dt>
                  <dd><p>Use medium heat, a nonstick skillet, and enough oil. Let the bottom brown before flipping for maximum crispiness.</p></dd>
                  
                  <dt>→ Can I use a different herb instead of dill?</dt>
                  <dd><p>Yes, chives or parsley work well if dill isn't available, offering a fresh flavor for the cream sauce.</p></dd>
                  
                  <dt>→ Is this dish gluten-free?</dt>
                  <dd><p>It can be made gluten-free by using a suitable flour blend in place of regular flour.</p></dd>
                  
                  <dt>→ What type of cheese works best?</dt>
                  <dd><p>Cheddar and Mozzarella are both great, but you can experiment with your favorite melting cheeses.</p></dd>
                  
                  <dt>→ Can I prepare the dill sauce ahead of time?</dt>
                  <dd><p>Absolutely! Store the sauce covered in the refrigerator for up to a day for best flavor.</p></dd>
                  
                  <dt>→ How should leftovers be stored?</dt>
                  <dd><p>Keep leftover cabbage pie in an airtight container in the fridge and reheat in a skillet for best texture.</p></dd>
                  
                </dl>
